text: The Harding Schoolhouse, in Corson County, South Dakota near Trail City, was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1989. It is a wood frame schoolhouse built in 1931, a late date for such a structure. With . It is located about west and north of Trail City. ==References== Category:Schools in South Dakota Category:National Register of Historic Places in Corson County, South Dakota
title: Harding Schoolhouse
